  "technicalDetails": "<p>Features:</p><ul><li> Fix the import issue of root bone scale being 100.0 when importing from Blender or other applications that don&#39;t use CM as the scale unit by rescaling the Skeletal mesh and applying a uniform scale to the root bone.</li><li>Fix&#39;s the issue when editing skeletal mesh physics asset bodies, if the root scale is not 1.0 then editor bodies becomes a hassle since every body transform is actually 100x smaller than visual scale.</li><li> Requires reapplying when you reimport the mesh.</li><li>Can apply selectively to a individual mesh that you may import at a later date for the skeleton and need to rescale it too.</li></ul><p>Code Modules:</p><ul><li> MeshScaleFixerEditor - Editor Only</li></ul><p>Number of Blueprints:0</p><p>Number of C&#43;&#43; Classes:5</p><p>Network Replicated: N/A</p><p>Supported Development Platforms: Win64</p><p>Supported Target Build Platforms: N/A - Editor only</p><p>Documentation: <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/e/2PACX-1vScRSd27RRQQhQhWyCY0tdl5X_GchIXJfbPoKQeimdz9AhriYfYp-vpE6JmgRNMekHyJd9M1Nrpl7gL/pub\" rel=\"nofollow\">Docs</a></p>",
